1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,250
I had suspicions that they wanted me to work with them

2
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:08,250
And I would not work with them, and I stayed that way, thank God

3
00:00:08,291 --> 00:00:10,791
Interviewer: Did they ask you to work with them directly?

4
00:00:10,916 --> 00:00:15,250
No, but through their questions it became clear they wanted me to work with them

5
00:00:15,625 --> 00:00:16,916
Interviewer: What did he say to you, for example?

6
00:00:17,291 --> 00:00:24,000
He said, For example, we have wounded people. Can you insert an IV cannula for them?

7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,125
Or give them injections

8
00:00:25,250 --> 00:00:28,291
I told them I don't have a license to do that, and I was afraid, and so on

9
00:00:28,791 --> 00:00:30,500
And that I had sworn not to give an injection to anyone

10
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Interviewer: So they asked you to help them according to your medical specialty?

11
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,291
Yes, but I didn't leave them any room for that and I didn't work with them

12
00:00:40,041 --> 00:00:43,083
Interviewer: So they didn’t ask you to join them and pledge allegiance directly?

13
00:00:43,083 --> 00:00:47,083
Yes, not directly

14
00:00:47,666 --> 00:00:50,125
I felt they wanted me to work with them

15
00:00:50,625 --> 00:00:52,500
But I didn't give them any room and I didn't work with them

16
00:00:52,916 --> 00:00:57,166
Interviewer: After they’d completed the interrogation with you in this hall inside this building

17
00:00:57,625 --> 00:00:59,125
Where did they take you after that?

18
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:03,291
They took me to a holding house, which was the house of Raed Jobbo

19
00:01:03,791 --> 00:01:05,291
Which was basically a house used as a prison

20
00:01:06,250 --> 00:01:12,375
They put us into a religious course for 10 days

21
00:01:12,791 --> 00:01:14,375
After these 10 days

22
00:01:14,916 --> 00:01:20,250
My detention then totaled 38 days, then they released me
